    <abstract>APPL interview with Andrea Ludden, administrator of the Salt &amp; Pepper 
        Museum and Gatlinburg resident. Ludden discusses the the time prior to leaving 
        her home, the evacuation experience, and the return to Gatlinburg to assess damages. 
        Ludden recalls the community efforts that brought people together after the Chimney 
        Tops II Wildfires. This quote touches on some of the interview's main themes: 
        "After this, I didn't realize how connected we were in the community."</abstract>
